WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.625 --> 00:00:03.060
What is a behavioral report?

00:00:03.060 --> 00:00:05.750
There are several types
of behavioral reports.

00:00:05.750 --> 00:00:10.320
They show the performance of our
content, the action visitors took.

00:00:10.320 --> 00:00:14.120
It visualizes the path users
travel from one page to another or

00:00:14.120 --> 00:00:16.230
from one event to the next.

00:00:16.230 --> 00:00:18.860
In apps it will be
from screen to screen.

00:00:18.860 --> 00:00:24.560
These reports can help you discover what
potential content keeps user engaged.

00:00:24.560 --> 00:00:28.710
It also can help you
identify potential issues.

00:00:28.710 --> 00:00:32.950
Okay, let's see how to use it.

00:00:32.950 --> 00:00:37.760
Here, we just click in
the behavioral pane on Overview, and

00:00:37.760 --> 00:00:40.878
we'll get the first report.

00:00:40.878 --> 00:00:43.980
The Overview gives you
a high level summary

00:00:43.980 --> 00:00:48.430
of what users interact with your site or
app.

00:00:48.430 --> 00:00:50.440
For instance,
here you can see the page views,

00:00:50.440 --> 00:00:54.790
the unique, time on page,
bounce rate, and many more.

00:00:54.790 --> 00:01:00.275
If you want to see the full report, just
go to the bottom and click, and you'll

00:01:00.275 --> 00:01:05.364
get all the detailed scenarios and
data of what happened with your site.

00:01:05.364 --> 00:01:10.704
Another very useful report
is the behavioral flow.

00:01:10.704 --> 00:01:12.310
If you clicked on it,

00:01:12.310 --> 00:01:18.560
you'll what are the paths that users
took when they traveled your site?

00:01:18.560 --> 00:01:23.580
This report could help you
identify potential problems or

00:01:23.580 --> 00:01:26.340
where are the pages that
the users are most engaged with

